  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Counter Trafficking in Persons and Smuggling of Migrants through Victims of Trafficking (VoT) Crisis Shelter Rehabilitation and Building Immigration Department&#x2019;s Capacities in Lesotho</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of this project is to contribute to sustainable peace and security, improve human security of vulnerable communities and mobile populations through addressing trafficking in persons, smuggling of migrants as well as supporting Government of Lesotho to start the initial discussions on reintegration support to forced returned migrants or so-called &apos;&apos;deportees&apos;&apos; in Lesotho.  This project is an urgent intervention to address Lesotho&apos;s downgraded status in the 2019 Trafficking in Persons (TiP) Report published by United States State Department. The increasing number of irregular migration from and to Lesotho, including smuggling of migrants from some African and Asian countries, as well as forced returned migrants or &apos;&apos;deportees&apos;&apos; from Republic of South Africa.</narrative>
  </description>
